We consider a series of RF pulses with constant flip angle α and variable phases φ k , separated by a constant time interval TR.

The phase ϑ, which is accumulated during each repetition period as a consequence of off-resonance effects and unbalanced gradients, is assumed to be constant in time. In the presence of crusher gradients, it will, however, strongly depend on the intravoxel position.
