m (0) has been determined as the magnetization immediately after the excitation pulse. In some sequences like PSIF, the crusher gradient is applied before the readout period and the signal has the characteristics of a spin echo. The corresponding magnetization can be obviously obtained from m (0) by undoing the last α-pulse: R x (−α) m (0) .
